Update Fibery entity with specified fields.

IMPORTANT: You MUST include "fibery/id" field to identify which entity to update.

FIELD NAMING:
- Use full field names in "Space/FieldName" format (e.g., "Product Management/Name")
- System fields use "fibery/" prefix (e.g., "fibery/id")
- Workflow state field: "workflow/state"

FIELD TYPES:
- Text fields: Use string values
- Workflow/Enum fields: Use string literal of the enum value (e.g., "To Do", "In Progress")
- Rich Text fields: Use object with "append" (boolean) and "content" (string)
  - {"append": false, "content": "New content"} - replaces entire content
  - {"append": true, "content": "Additional text"} - appends to existing content
- Relation fields: Use object with "fibery/id" (e.g., {"fibery/id": "uuid-here"})

EXAMPLES (note, that these databases are non-existent, use databases only from user's schema!):

Example 1: Simple field update
{
    "database": "Product Management/Feature",
    "entity": {
        "fibery/id": "12345678-1234-5678-1234-567812345678",
        "Product Management/Name": "Updated Feature Name",
        "workflow/state": "In Progress"
    }
}

Example 2: Update with Rich Text append
{
    "database": "Software Development/Task",
    "entity": {
        "fibery/id": "12345678-1234-5678-1234-567812345678",
        "Software Development/name": "Fix login bug",
        "Software Development/Description": {"append": true, "content": "\n\nNotes: Fixed by updating authentication logic"},
        "workflow/state": "Done"
    }
}

RESULT:
In case of successful execution, you will get a link to updated entity. Make sure to give that link to the user.